The Naira appreciated slightly by 0.07 per cent to N364.02 per dollar at the Investors and Exporters (I&E) foreign exchange window on Thursday. At the I&E FX window a total of $135.47mn was traded in 399 deals, with rates ranging between $/N358.00 – $/N365.00. The local currency at the Interbank remained stable at N306.45 at the dollar and $/N361.34 (SMIS). At the parallel market, the cash and transfer rates remained unchanged at $/N360.00 and $/N363.00 respectively. © 2018, Hallmarknews. All rights reserved. Reference and link to this site is required if you wish to reuse any article. 0 comments and opinions